SIMPLE: pigeonhole
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pigeonhole
<hw>Pi"geon*hole`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A small
compartment in a desk or case for the keeping of letters, documents,
etc.; -- so called from the resemblance of a row of them to the
compartments in a dovecote.</def> <rj><au>Burke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pigeonhole</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pigeonhole
<hw>Pi"geon*hole`</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To place in the pigeonhole
of a case or cabinet; hence, to put away; to lay aside indefinitely;
<as>as, to <ex>pigeonhole</ex> a letter or a report</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pigeon-livered</ent>⟦br⟧
